        <p>We protect personal information regardless of the format. Specific procedures are in place for communicating by phone, email, fax, and post/courier.</p>
        <p>We retain patient records as required by law and professional regulations.</p>
        <p>How do we dispose of information when it is no longer required? When information is no longer required, it is destroyed in a secure manner, according to set procedures that govern the storage and destruction of personal information.</p>
        <h4>Complaints Process</h4>
        <p>
          If you believe that this office has not replied to your access request or has not handled your personal information in a reasonable manner, please address your concerns with a Medeo Corporation office assistant. If you would like more information about our privacy protection practices, you should also contact us and we will take steps to endeavor to provide you with that information.
        </p>
        <p>You may also choose to make a complaint to the provincial privacy commissioner. Prior to taking this step please ensure you have addressed your concerns to Medeo Corporation and allowed reasonable time for response.</p>
